# Messaging (SQS + EventBridge)

Async work flows through SQS to the worker Lambda; scheduled work fires from EventBridge to the cron Lambda. Messages share one typed contract.

## Message contract

`packages/shared/src/types.ts` defines `QueueMessage<T>` (`type`, `payload`, `timestamp`, `traceId`). Producers and the worker import it via `@repo/shared/types` — keep both sides on this type.

## Worker (`apps/worker/src/index.ts`)

SQS-triggered handler returning `SQSBatchResponse`. It loops `event.Records`, parses each body as `QueueMessage`, and on error pushes `{ itemIdentifier: record.messageId }` to `batchItemFailures` (partial batch failure — only failed messages are retried, not the whole batch). This relies on the event source mapping's `function_response_types = ["ReportBatchItemFailures"]` in `infra/modules/sqs/main.tf`. That module also provisions a DLQ (`<queue>-dlq`, 14-day retention) with `maxReceiveCount = 3` redrive.

## Cron (`apps/cron/src/index.ts`)

`ScheduledEvent` handler invoked by the EventBridge rule (`infra/modules/eventbridge/main.tf`). Schedule is the module's `schedule_expression` var (default `rate(1 hour)`).

## Add a message type

1. Extend/narrow `QueueMessage` in `packages/shared/src/types.ts` (e.g. a `type` union with typed `payload`).
2. Handle the new `message.type` in the worker's `processMessage`.
3. Enqueue with `SendMessageCommand` against `queue_url` (root Terraform output), sending a JSON-stringified `QueueMessage`; grant the producer's Lambda role `sqs:SendMessage`.
